# Introduction to cybersecurity

This repository documents my journey learning cybersecurity fundamentals, including both theoretical knowledge and practical exercises.

## Overview
Cybersecurity involves protecting systems, networks, and data from digital attacks. This repository serves as a record of my learning progress as I build skills in this field.

## Topics Covered
- Introduction to Cybersecurity
- Networking Basics (IP, DNS, HTTP/HTTPS)
- Common Threats:
  - Phishing
  - Malware
  - Ransomware
  - Social Engineering
- Vulnerabilities and Risk Management
- Basic Security Practices

## Linux Practice
- Basic terminal commands (ls, cd, pwd, mkdir, rm)
- File and directory management
- User permissions
- Navigation in the Linux environment

## Tools I Am Learning
- Linux (command line)
- Nmap (network scanning)
- Wireshark (network analysis - beginner)

